docs.abstract: Apple’s spreadsheet program can edit Microsoft Excel files, but you need to take an extra step to use those files in Excel again.
docs.snippet: Apple’s spreadsheet program can edit Microsoft Excel files, but you need to take an extra step to use those files in Excel again.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. My wife and I have used Apple’s Numbers program to open and edit Microsoft Excel files. But how can Excel subsequently be used to open and edit the same file after it’s been opened in Numbers?

headline.main: Converting Spreadsheets in Apple’s Numbers to Excel

docs.abstract: Many other programs and online software services can open, view and even edit spreadsheets created by Microsoft’s flagship business application.

docs.lead_paragraph: Q. What other programs can open Excel files?

docs.abstract: Monster Worldwide, a former competitor of LinkedIn, has been sold to Randstad Holding of the Netherlands for a fraction of its former value.
docs.snippet: Monster Worldwide, a former competitor of LinkedIn, has been sold to Randstad Holding of the Netherlands for a fraction of its former value.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft has just been given a big warning about its $26 billion deal for LinkedIn, the professional social-networking site. The software giant’s June bid already looked pricey, but the fate of an erstwhile LinkedIn competitor offers a cautionary tale of how bad things could get.

headline.main: In Buying LinkedIn, Microsoft Might Pay Heed to Monster

docs.abstract: As big companies race to build oversize data networks, communities are finding that the giant buildings can operate with only about 30 people.
docs.snippet: As big companies race to build oversize data networks, communities are finding that the giant buildings can operate with only about 30 people.
docs.lead_paragraph: BOYDTON, Va. — A giant Microsoft facility just outside this very small town hides behind a quarter-mile berm and a guard house, across the highway from the rubble of a demolished prison.

headline.main: Cloud Computing Brings Sprawling Centers, but Few Jobs, to Small Towns
